# Layout Patterns

## Standard Section Container

Every section follows this two-layer pattern:

```css
.section {
  width: 100%;
  padding: var(--section-padding) 0;
}

.inner {
  max-width: var(--content-width);
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding-inline: var(--page-padding);
}
```

- `--content-width` = 1440px
- `--page-padding` = 80px
- `--section-padding` = 120px

## Full-Bleed Right Pattern

Used when content (e.g. blog carousel cards) needs to extend past the right edge of the content container:

```css
.section {
  overflow: hidden;
}

.inner {
  padding-left: max(var(--page-padding), calc((100vw - var(--content-width)) / 2 + var(--page-padding)));
  padding-right: 0;
}
```

## Footer Layout

- Flex columns with `border-bottom: 1px solid #333` as row separators
- Each row: `padding: 52px 0`
- Top row: `display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: flex-start;`
- Bottom row (capabilities/industries): `display: flex; gap: 80px;`

## Responsive Breakpoints

Three breakpoints — desktop first:

| Name    | Query                    | Key changes                              |
|---------|--------------------------|------------------------------------------|
| Desktop | Default                  | Full layout, `--page-padding: 80px`      |
| Tablet  | `@media (max-width: 1024px)` | Stack columns, reduce padding to 40px |
| Mobile  | `@media (max-width: 767px)`  | Single column, reduce padding to 24px  |

At **tablet** (≤ 1024px):
- Multi-column layouts switch to `flex-wrap: wrap` or single column
- Page padding reduces: `padding-inline: 40px`
- Section padding reduces: `padding: 80px 0`
- Font sizes scale down proportionally

At **mobile** (≤ 767px):
- All layouts are single column
- Page padding reduces: `padding-inline: 24px`
- Section padding reduces: `padding: 60px 0`
- Hero headings cap at `32px`
